17 SECTION 4. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1151.25a of Title 59, unless
19 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 A. Except as otherwise provided in the Roofing Contractor
21 Registration Act, on and after the effective date of this act, every
22 roofing contractor, except for those defined in subsection G of this
23 section, offering to engage in or engaging in performing residential
24 roofing contractor work in this state shall be required to receive a
Req. No. 1864 Page 18

1 resi dential roofing endorsement. To receive a residential roofing
2 endorsement, the roofing contractor shall be required to take and
3 successfully pass a residential roofing examination approved under
4 the provisions of this act with a minimum score of seventy percent
5 (70%), and be in compliance with all other provisions of this act
6 and rules before acting or being endorsed as a residential roofing
7 contractor. For applicants who have been registered and in good
8 standing with the Construction Industries Board on the effective
9 date of this act, there shall be a twelve-month grandfathering-in
10 period from the effective date of this act to either pass the exam
11 or complete an additional ten (10) hours of continuing education
12 credits approved in advance by the Committee of Roofing Examiners
13 and the Construction Industries Board, to be granted a residential
14 roofer endorsement.
15 B. Examinations for a residential roofer endorsement shall be
16 uniform and practical in nature and sufficiently strict to test the
17 qualifications and fitness of the applicants for endorsement.
18 Examinations shall be in whole or in part in writing. Examinations
19 shall be offered at least monthly; dates, times, and locations shall
20 be determined by the registrar or third-party vendor with approval
21 of the registrar.
22 C. Any applicant initially failing to pass the examination
23 shall not be permitted to take another examination for a period of
24 thirty (30) days. Any applicant subsequently failing to pass the
Req. No. 1864 Page 19

1 exam ination shall not be permitted to take another examination for a
2 period of ninety (90) days. However, in a declared state of
3 emergency, the examination shall be available as often as possible
4 as determined by the registrar.
5 D. No residential roofer endorsement shall be renewed unless
6 the qualifying party has completed the required hours of continuing
7 education pursuant to subsection A of this section.
8 E. For all new applicants not registered and in good standing
9 with the Construction Industries Board prior to the effective date
